{
  "texts": [
    "Synthetic images have become very common in the field of Computer Vision (CV) for a large variety of real-world applications (Meharban et al. 2021; Dong et al. 201; Pratt et al. 1978; Frolov et al. 2021; Nikolenko 2021).",
    "To the best of our knowledge, they firstly appeared in the CV literature in a work by Pratt et al. (1978).",
    "Synthetic data were originally used to ease the analysis and comparison of image processing methods through the generation of images from Communicated by Jingdong Wang.",
    "B Rita Delussu rita.delussu@unica.it B Lorenzo Putzu lorenzo.putzu@unica.it B Giorgio Fumera fumera@unica.it 1 Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, University of Cagliari, via Marengo, 09123 Cagliari, Italy a model under strictly controlled conditions (e.g., in terms of textures, materials and light), according to the so-called analysis by synthesis approach (Pratt et al. 1978; Horn and Schunck 1981; Woodham et al. 1985).",
    "Since then, the interest in synthetic data has considerably increased in CV, as well as in other fields, as witnessed by the ever-increasing number of publications (see image on top of Fig. 1)."
  ]
}